erospace, construction, and pharmaceuticals. Furthermore, it provides industrial applications, LNG infrastructure, horsepower, automotive industry applications systems, and LNG equipment, as well as beer kegs. The company serves aviation and aerospace, construction and cement, cryo scientific research, dairy and livestock, electronics, fertilizer and chemical, food and beverages, material handling, glass and ceramics, health care and life sciences, hydrogen, industrial gas, LNG and LCNG, metal processing, oil and gas, refining, petrochemical, paper and pulp, pharmaceuticals, power and utilities, rubber, steel and mining, water and water treatment, and entertainment and event sectors. INOX India Limited was incorporated in 1976 and is headquartered in Vadodara, India."}}